parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle can move unexpectedly, potentially causing accidents or injuries, especially when the driver is outside the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle moves on its own
even when the driver is not in the vehicle
the vehicle accelerates or decelerates without input from the driver
the vehicle shifts into gear without the driver's intention.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hybrid system can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to reduced acceleration, loss of regenerative braking, and potentially causing accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle has reduced power
the vehicle will not start the gas engine
the regenerative braking system is disabled
the vehicle operates only on electric power at a severely reduced level
multiple warning lights appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the charging system can cause electrical fires, damage to the vehicle's electrical components, and potentially harm the driver or passengers.
symptoms: The charger supplied by the manufacturer melts during normal charging
the cord is damaged
there is a loose plug terminal and hot spot
the vehicle's electrical system is damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Limited Propulsion Power in High Temperatures
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle's reduced propulsion power in high temperatures can cause a loss of speed, making it difficult to maintain a safe speed, especially on uphill roads, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle slows down to a low speed (around 20 mph)
a "Limited Propulsion" message appears on the dashboard
and the vehicle may struggle to maintain speed on uphill roads.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission to shift into gear can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to shift into park
the vehicle fails to shift into gear
the transmission slips or hesitates
and the vehicle may stall or lose power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration and braking can cause the vehicle to lose control, increasing the risk of accidents, and potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates on its own
the vehicle brakes suddenly without warning
and the vehicle may exhibit unpredictable behavior.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the forward collision mitigation system can cause the vehicle to brake suddenly or unnecessarily, increasing the risk of accidents, and potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle's brakes are applied suddenly and unnecessarily
the vehicle's forward collision mitigation system activates falsely
and the vehicle may exhibit unpredictable behavior.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of unrelated systems, such as the wiper system, can cause distractions and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The wiper system activates unnecessarily
and other unrelated systems may malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected reduction of propulsion power can cause the vehicle to slow down or lose power, potentially leading to accidents, especially when driving on highways or uphill.
symptoms: The "Propulsion Reduced" warning light illuminates
the vehicle suddenly loses power or speed
the vehicle slows down without driver input
the electric charge indicator shows zero miles remaining despite a full tank of gas.
